MAD MADAME MIM (IRE) stalked the pace inside, tipped out in upper stretch, bid four wide nearing the eighth pole, was impeded soon after, switched back to the left lead, regathered herself and was gaining late to gain the place in the final strides. BREAKING BULLET saved ground off the pace, bid at the rail in midstretch and was narrowly outfinished. ELISSA JOE vied inside of foes, drifted out under left-handed urging nearing the eighth pole, bumped ROMASHKA and weakened. ACQUIRED TASTE chased the pace four wide and lacked the needed rally. SAMURAI'SDON'TCRY was outrun inside. EMPIRE GIRL pressed the pace three wide and tired in the lane. LUMINANT was steadied twice early, raced three wide and never threatened. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY AND AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF MAD MADAME MIM, ROMASHKA WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST FOR INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH AND PLACED SECOND.
